1247
01:22:22,646 --> 01:22:23,812
Some more bread.

1248
01:22:23,980 --> 01:22:26,398
Tomorrow we eat sandwiches.
You got to go on a diet, Vinnie.

1249
01:22:26,566 --> 01:22:28,651
-You must be kidding.
-Believe me.

1250
01:22:37,911 --> 01:22:39,328
What are you doing?

1251
01:22:44,668 --> 01:22:46,543
I'll take that.

1252
01:22:48,922 --> 01:22:51,382
-All right, I'll catch you guys later.
-Yeah.

1253
01:22:51,549 --> 01:22:53,884
You going for a walk in the park?

1254
01:22:55,387 --> 01:22:58,555
-Okay, I'll catch you next week. Thanks.
-Okay.

1255
01:23:01,393 --> 01:23:03,936
-Is there any more?
-No, that's it. Have a good weekend.

1256
01:23:04,104 --> 01:23:05,312
-Thanks.
-You too, Henry.

1257
01:23:14,114 --> 01:23:15,155
Mrs. Hill, come here.

1258
01:23:15,323 --> 01:23:16,490
Come on.

1259
01:23:19,869 --> 01:23:21,912
You girls stay right here.

1260
01:23:22,330 --> 01:23:25,582
-I want you to hold hands.
-Okay, go right up to the front.

1261
01:23:25,917 --> 01:23:27,835
- Let's go.
- How you doing?

1262
01:23:28,003 --> 01:23:30,212
- Good, how are you?
- Very well, thank you.

1263
01:23:42,475 --> 01:23:44,935
-What you talking about?
-I saw her name in the register.

1264
01:23:45,103 --> 01:23:47,271
- Jesus Christ.
- You want her to visit you?

1265
01:23:47,439 --> 01:23:51,108
Let her stay up all night crying
and writing letters to the parole board.

1266
01:23:51,276 --> 01:23:54,445
What am I doing here?
Where am I? I'm in jail.

1267
01:23:54,612 --> 01:23:56,739
I can't stop people
from coming to see me.

1268
01:23:56,906 --> 01:24:00,284
Good, let her sneak this stuff in
for you every week.

1269
01:24:00,452 --> 01:24:04,079
-Let her fight these bastards every week!
-Look what you're doing! Stop it!

1270
01:24:05,832 --> 01:24:07,791
- Shh.
- I'm sorry.

1271
01:24:08,293 --> 01:24:10,753
Let her sneak this shit in for you.

1272
01:24:11,796 --> 01:24:13,630
Will you stop it, Karen?

1273
01:24:14,090 --> 01:24:16,633
-Let her do it!
-Stop it!

1274
01:24:24,809 --> 01:24:28,103
Nobody's helping me. I'm all alone.

1275
01:24:29,147 --> 01:24:31,148
Belle and Morrie are broke.

1276
01:24:31,566 --> 01:24:34,777
I asked your friend Remo
for the money that he owes you.

1277
01:24:34,944 --> 01:24:36,320
You know what he told me?

1278
01:24:36,488 --> 01:24:40,074
He told me to take my kids down
to the police station and get on welfare.

1279
01:24:40,241 --> 01:24:42,201
It's gonna be okay.

1280
01:24:42,410 --> 01:24:46,497
Even Paulie, since he got out, I've never
seen him. I never see anybody anymore.

1281
01:24:46,664 --> 01:24:49,458
It's only you and me.
That's what happens when you go away.

1282
01:24:49,626 --> 01:24:53,629
I told you that we're on our own.
Forget everybody else. Forget Paulie.

1283
01:24:54,631 --> 01:24:58,634
As long as he's on parole,
he doesn't want anybody doing anything.

1284
01:25:01,096 --> 01:25:03,347
-I can't do it.
-Yes, you can. Listen to me.

1285
01:25:03,515 --> 01:25:06,100
All I need for you
is to keep bringing me the stuff.

1286
01:25:06,267 --> 01:25:08,852
I got a guy in here from Pittsburgh
who'll help me move it.

1287
01:25:09,020 --> 01:25:10,646
In a month we're gonna be fine.

1288
01:25:10,814 --> 01:25:13,148
-We won't need anybody.
-I'm afraid.

1289
01:25:13,316 --> 01:25:15,234
I'm afraid if Paulie finds out....

1290
01:25:15,401 --> 01:25:16,819
Don't worry about him.

1291
01:25:16,986 --> 01:25:20,531
He is not helping us out.
Is he putting any food on the table?

1292
01:25:21,699 --> 01:25:23,158
We've gotta help each other.

1293
01:25:23,326 --> 01:25:26,995
We've just gotta be really careful
while we do it.

1294
01:25:31,668 --> 01:25:33,877
I don't want to hear a word
about her anymore.

1295
01:25:34,045 --> 01:25:35,087
Never.

1296
01:26:00,655 --> 01:26:02,114
Daddy!

1297
01:26:03,741 --> 01:26:05,993
- We missed you.
- Are you here to stay?

1298
01:26:06,161 --> 01:26:09,746
Did you see our pictures?
I did the one with the house and rainbow.

1299
01:26:09,914 --> 01:26:11,331
I did the sun.

1300
01:26:11,499 --> 01:26:15,419
My chorus concert is in two weeks.
Are you coming?

1301
01:26:16,254 --> 01:26:18,088
Do you like the house?

1302
01:26:19,382 --> 01:26:21,258
Karen, get packed.
We're moving out of here.

1303
01:26:21,426 --> 01:26:22,634
With what?

1304
01:26:22,844 --> 01:26:25,929
Don't worry, with what.
Just start looking for a new house.

1305
01:26:26,097 --> 01:26:29,516
I got to go to Pittsburgh in the morning.
Those guys there owe me $15,000.

1306
01:26:29,684 --> 01:26:31,602
We'll be all right. I got things lined up.

1307
01:26:31,769 --> 01:26:34,438
Pittsburgh? You have to go see
your parole officer tomorrow.

1308
01:26:34,606 --> 01:26:37,524
Don't worry about it.
Everything's gonna be fine.

1309
01:26:38,234 --> 01:26:40,360
- Who wants to go to Uncle Paulie's?
- Me!

1310
01:26:50,914 --> 01:26:52,497
What do you want?

1311
01:26:52,749 --> 01:26:54,791
Sweetheart, let Mommy eat.

1312
01:26:58,254 --> 01:27:01,131
You look good.
Did you eat this good in the joint?

1313
01:27:03,259 --> 01:27:05,093
I don't want any more of that shit.

1314
01:27:05,261 --> 01:27:06,303
What shit?

1315
01:27:06,471 --> 01:27:09,097
-Just stay away from the garbage.
-Look, Paulie--

1316
01:27:09,265 --> 01:27:12,434
I'm not talking about what you did inside.
You did what you had to do.

1317
01:27:12,602 --> 01:27:14,895
I'm talking about now. From now.
Here and now.

1318
01:27:16,189 --> 01:27:18,941
-Why would I get into that?
-Don't make a jerk out of me.

1319
01:27:19,108 --> 01:27:20,651
Just don't do it.

1320
01:27:24,405 --> 01:27:27,366
I want to talk to you about Jimmy.
You gotta watch out for him.

1321
01:27:27,533 --> 01:27:30,494
He's a good earner, but he's wild,
takes too many chances.

1322
01:27:30,662 --> 01:27:32,829
I know Jimmy. You think
I would take chances like him?

1323
01:27:32,997 --> 01:27:34,790
Tommy's a good kid, but he's crazy.

1324
01:27:34,958 --> 01:27:36,583
He's a cowboy.
He's got too much to prove.

1325
01:27:36,751 --> 01:27:38,543
You gotta watch out for kids like this.

1326
01:27:38,711 --> 01:27:41,338
I know what they are.
I only use them for certain things.

1327
01:27:41,506 --> 01:27:44,007
I ain't gonna get fucked like Gribbs,
you understand?

1328
01:27:44,175 --> 01:27:48,512
Gribbs is 70 years old. The fucking guy's
gonna die in prison. I don't need that.

1329
01:27:48,846 --> 01:27:52,724
So I'm warning everybody. Everybody.
Could be my son, could be anybody.

1330
01:27:53,268 --> 01:27:55,811
Gribbs got 20 years just
for saying hello to some fuck...

1331
01:27:55,979 --> 01:27:58,063
who was sneaking behind his back,
selling junk.

1332
01:27:58,231 --> 01:28:00,691
I don't need that.
That won't happen to me, understand?

1333
01:28:00,858 --> 01:28:03,110
You know you're out early
because I got you a job.

1334
01:28:03,278 --> 01:28:05,153
I don't need this heat,
you understand that?

1335
01:28:05,321 --> 01:28:09,032
You see anybody fucking around
with this shit you're gonna tell me, right?

1336
01:28:09,200 --> 01:28:10,242
That means anybody.

1337
01:28:10,410 --> 01:28:11,451
-All right.
-Yeah?

1338
01:28:11,619 --> 01:28:13,328
Yeah. Of course.

1339
01:28:20,920 --> 01:28:22,879
Took me about a week
of sneaking around...

1340
01:28:23,047 --> 01:28:24,881
before I could unload
the Pittsburgh stuff.

1341
01:28:25,049 --> 01:28:27,509
But when I did, it was a real score.

1342
01:28:27,677 --> 01:28:30,220
I started using Sandy's place
to mix the stuff.

1343
01:28:30,388 --> 01:28:32,806
And even with Sandy snorting
more than she mixed...

1344
01:28:32,974 --> 01:28:35,600
I could see that
this was a really good business.

1345
01:28:35,768 --> 01:28:38,186
I made $12,000 in my second week.

1346
01:28:38,771 --> 01:28:41,857
I had a down payment on my house
and things were really rolling.

1347
01:28:42,025 --> 01:28:46,236
All I had to do was every once in a while
tell Sandy that I loved her.

1348
01:28:49,866 --> 01:28:51,908
But it was perfect, I'm telling you.

1349
01:28:52,076 --> 01:28:54,453
As long as I kept getting
the stuff from Pittsburgh...

1350
01:28:54,620 --> 01:28:56,330
I knew Paulie would never find out.

1351
01:28:56,497 --> 01:29:00,375
Within a couple of weeks,
it got so big I needed some help.

1352
01:29:00,752 --> 01:29:03,545
So I got Jimmy and Tommy
to come in with me.

1353
01:29:03,921 --> 01:29:05,464
It's fucking great.

1354
01:29:05,798 --> 01:29:06,923
Mr. Conway.

1355
01:29:12,764 --> 01:29:14,681
-Bring your pay slips?
-Yeah.

1356
01:29:17,769 --> 01:29:20,103
Four and a half months of dirt.

1357
01:29:20,688 --> 01:29:23,231
- It's so good.
- I did it.

1358
01:29:24,400 --> 01:29:26,985
- Do you love it?
- It's wonderful.

1359
01:29:27,445 --> 01:29:31,198
And this we just had to have
made special. Go ahead, sit in it, Belle.

1360
01:29:31,366 --> 01:29:33,909
The others you couldn't even sit in.

1361
01:29:34,118 --> 01:29:35,619
Okay, you ready?

1362
01:29:35,787 --> 01:29:37,954
Watch the wall with the rock.

1363
01:29:45,588 --> 01:29:48,382
