I'll take you home, then look for him.

1630
01:46:30,300 --> 01:46:32,551
I've been home! I've been on the phone--

1631
01:46:32,719 --> 01:46:34,011
He's playing cards.

1632
01:46:37,140 --> 01:46:39,642
-What'll I tell Belle?
-Who gives a fuck?

1633
01:46:40,519 --> 01:46:43,979
Tell her he ran off with some broad.
What do you care?

1634
01:46:44,147 --> 01:46:46,190
-Watch this.
-Don't fuck with them.

1635
01:46:46,358 --> 01:46:48,317
I do it all the time. I'll bust their balls.

1636
01:46:48,485 --> 01:46:51,320
Don't give them the satisfaction,
the fucks.

1637
01:46:53,824 --> 01:46:55,866
Come on, fuckos. Let's go for a ride.

1638
01:46:57,452 --> 01:46:59,161
Keep them up all night.

1639
01:47:00,080 --> 01:47:01,664
I'll see you later.

1640
01:47:51,339 --> 01:47:54,508
Jimmy was cutting every link
between himself and the robbery...

1641
01:47:54,676 --> 01:47:57,052
but it had nothing to do with me.

1642
01:48:07,564 --> 01:48:10,900
I gave Jimmy the tip and he gave me
some Christmas money.

1643
01:48:12,652 --> 01:48:15,029
From then on, I kept my mouth shut.

1644
01:48:15,197 --> 01:48:19,074
I knew Jimmy.
He had the cash. It was his.

1645
01:48:19,242 --> 01:48:22,578
He kicked some money upstairs to Paulie,
but that was it.

1646
01:48:23,663 --> 01:48:27,124
It made him sick to turn the money over
to the guys who stole it.

1647
01:48:27,292 --> 01:48:30,127
He'd rather whack them.
Anyway, what did I care?

1648
01:48:30,295 --> 01:48:32,129
I wasn't asking for anything.

1649
01:48:32,297 --> 01:48:35,925
And Jimmy was making nice money
through my Pittsburgh connections.

1650
01:48:36,468 --> 01:48:40,554
Still, months after the robbery
they were finding bodies all over.

1651
01:49:02,577 --> 01:49:05,287
When they found Carbone
in the meat truck...

1652
01:49:05,455 --> 01:49:07,122
he was frozen so stiff...

1653
01:49:07,290 --> 01:49:10,417
it took them two days
to thaw him out for the autopsy.

1654
01:49:15,257 --> 01:49:17,383
Still, I never saw Jimmy so happy.

1655
01:49:17,801 --> 01:49:21,387
He was like a kid. We had money
coming in through my Pittsburgh people...

1656
01:49:21,555 --> 01:49:25,099
and even after a while,
the Lufthansa thing began to calm down.

1657
01:49:25,267 --> 01:49:27,434
What made Jimmy so happy
that morning...

1658
01:49:27,602 --> 01:49:30,479
was that this was the day
that Tommy was being made.

1659
01:49:30,981 --> 01:49:33,983
Jimmy was so excited,
you'd think he was being made.

1660
01:49:34,609 --> 01:49:37,236
He must have made four calls
to Tommy's house.

1661
01:49:37,445 --> 01:49:41,365
They had a signal set up, so he'd know
the minute the ceremony was over.

1662
01:49:42,242 --> 01:49:44,493
- Ma, where are you?
- Here I am.

1663
01:49:45,120 --> 01:49:47,663
-You're home.
-Home? I'm leaving.

1664
01:49:48,123 --> 01:49:50,666
-You look lovely.
-I look good, huh?

1665
01:49:50,834 --> 01:49:54,211
You look wonderful. Be careful.
Congratulations.

1666
01:49:54,879 --> 01:49:58,215
I love you. Don't paint
any more religious pictures, please.

1667
01:49:58,383 --> 01:50:00,009
-God be with you.
-Bye, Ma.

1668
01:50:00,176 --> 01:50:02,511
We always called each other goodfellas.

1669
01:50:02,679 --> 01:50:04,305
You'd say to somebody:

1670
01:50:04,472 --> 01:50:08,684
"You'll like this guy. He's all right.
He's a goodfella, one of us."

1671
01:50:09,019 --> 01:50:10,394
You understand?

1672
01:50:11,062 --> 01:50:13,272
We were goodfellas. Wiseguys.

1673
01:50:15,859 --> 01:50:19,236
But Jimmy and I could never be made
because we had Irish blood.

1674
01:50:19,404 --> 01:50:21,864
It didn't matter my mother was Sicilian.

1675
01:50:22,115 --> 01:50:26,035
To become a member of a crew,
you've got to be 100% Italian...

1676
01:50:26,202 --> 01:50:29,204
so they can trace your relatives
back to the old country.

1677
01:50:36,546 --> 01:50:38,881
It's the highest honor they can give you.

1678
01:50:39,049 --> 01:50:41,550
It means you belong
to a family and a crew.

1679
01:50:41,926 --> 01:50:44,470
It means nobody can fuck around
with you.

1680
01:50:45,013 --> 01:50:47,389
It also means you could
fuck around with anybody...

1681
01:50:47,557 --> 01:50:50,017
just as long as they aren't also a member.

1682
01:50:50,185 --> 01:50:53,604
It's like a license to steal.
A license to do anything.

1683
01:50:55,774 --> 01:50:57,775
How many years ago
since you were made?

1684
01:50:57,942 --> 01:51:00,694
- I'm an old-timer. 30 years ago.
- Thirty years?

1685
01:51:00,862 --> 01:51:05,115
Brings back a lot of memories.
Pike's Peak was a pimple then, wasn't it?

1686
01:51:08,411 --> 01:51:11,372
As far as Jimmy was concerned,
with Tommy being made...

1687
01:51:11,539 --> 01:51:13,916
it was like we were all being made.

1688
01:51:14,793 --> 01:51:17,336
We would now have
one of our own as a member.

1689
01:51:28,890 --> 01:51:30,099
Oh, no--

1690
01:51:33,103 --> 01:51:34,937
- Who's this?
- This is Vinnie.

1691
01:51:35,105 --> 01:51:37,940
Vinnie. What happened?
Did we get straightened out?

1692
01:51:38,108 --> 01:51:41,110
No, we had a problem.
We tried to do everything we could.

1693
01:51:41,277 --> 01:51:42,319
What do you mean?

1694
01:51:42,487 --> 01:51:46,615
You know what I mean. He's gone,
and we couldn't do nothing about it.

1695
01:51:48,493 --> 01:51:50,369
-That's it.
-What do you mean?

1696
01:51:50,537 --> 01:51:51,912
He's gone.

1697
01:51:53,873 --> 01:51:54,915
That's it.

1698
01:51:59,796 --> 01:52:02,631
I knew it! I can't fucking believe it.

1699
01:52:13,017 --> 01:52:15,144
-What happened?
-They fucking whacked him.

1700
01:52:15,311 --> 01:52:16,478
Fuck.

1701
01:52:32,328 --> 01:52:33,996
Are you all right?

1702
01:52:41,045 --> 01:52:43,547
It was revenge for Billy Batts...

1703
01:52:43,715 --> 01:52:45,466
and a lot of other things.

1704
01:52:45,633 --> 01:52:46,675
And that's that.

1705
01:52:46,843 --> 01:52:49,344
There was nothing we could do about it.

1706
01:52:49,512 --> 01:52:52,139
Batts was a made man
and Tommy wasn't.

1707
01:52:52,724 --> 01:52:54,516
We had to sit still and take it.

1708
01:52:54,684 --> 01:52:58,270
It was among the Italians.
It was real greaseball shit.

1709
01:53:10,909 --> 01:53:12,743
They even shot Tommy in the face...

1710
01:53:12,911 --> 01:53:16,371
so his mother couldn't give him
an open coffin at the funeral.

1711
01:54:03,878 --> 01:54:07,172
I was gonna be busy all day.
I had to drop off some guns at Jimmy's...

1712
01:54:07,340 --> 01:54:09,007
to match some silencers he had.

1713
01:54:09,175 --> 01:54:12,261
I had to pick up my brother at the hospital
and drive him home.

1714
01:54:12,428 --> 01:54:14,847
I had to pick up
some new Pittsburgh stuff for Lois...

1715
01:54:15,014 --> 01:54:18,267
to fly down to some customers
I had near Atlanta.

1716
01:54:29,571 --> 01:54:33,031
Right away, I knew he didn't want them,
and I'd be stuck for the money.

1717
01:54:33,199 --> 01:54:36,910
I only bought them because
he wanted them, and now he didn't.

1718
01:54:37,620 --> 01:54:41,123
What good are these? None of them fit.
What's the matter with you?

1719
01:54:41,291 --> 01:54:42,499
I'm not paying for it.

1720
01:54:42,667 --> 01:54:46,378
I didn't say a thing. Jimmy was
so pissed off, he didn't even say goodbye.

1721
01:54:46,546 --> 01:54:48,797
Stop the drugs. They're making
your mind into mush!

1722
01:54:48,965 --> 01:54:50,299
-You hear me?
-I'll take them back.

1723
01:55:04,022 --> 01:55:05,981
My Pittsburgh guys always wanted guns.

1724
01:55:06,149 --> 01:55:09,735
Since I would see them in the afternoon
to pick up a delivery...

1725
01:55:09,903 --> 01:55:12,487
I was pretty sure I'd get my money back.

1726
01:55:31,507 --> 01:55:32,591
Oh, my God.

1727
01:55:34,344 --> 01:55:38,388
When I finally got to the hospital,
Michael's doctor wanted to put me in bed.

1728
01:55:38,556 --> 01:55:40,682
Jesus Christ, what happened to you?

1729
01:55:41,726 --> 01:55:44,102
I almost got into an accident
on the way here.

1730
01:55:44,270 --> 01:55:47,189
And I told him I was partying all night.

1731
01:55:47,357 --> 01:55:49,149
-I'm fine.
-Come on. Get over here.

1732
01:55:49,317 --> 01:55:51,401
-Doc, I'm fine.
-Let me check you out.

1733
01:55:51,903 --> 01:55:53,070
Come on.

1734
01:55:56,115 --> 01:55:58,784
He took mercy on me,
gave me 10 milligrams of Valium...

1735
01:55:58,952 --> 01:56:00,035
and sent me home.

1736
01:56:00,745 --> 01:56:04,498
My plan was to drop off my brother
at the house and pick up Karen.

1737
01:56:06,542 --> 01:56:09,753
There it is.
You see that helicopter right there?

1738
01:56:09,921 --> 01:56:13,256
Right in front of us, there.
I think it's been following me all morning.

1739
01:56:13,424 --> 01:56:16,176
-Get the fuck out. What are you, nuts?
-I'm telling you.

1740
01:56:16,344 --> 01:56:17,803
I don't know what's going on.

1741
01:56:17,971 --> 01:56:20,847
It's the third time I've seen it.
At the hospital I saw it.

1742
01:56:21,015 --> 01:56:23,392
I had to make some stops.
I've seen it every time.

1743
01:56:23,559 --> 01:56:25,978
I've been all over town
and I've seen it all day.

1744
01:56:32,944 --> 01:56:34,569
I was cooking dinner that night.

1745
01:56:35,697 --> 01:56:39,366
I had to start braising the beef
and veal shanks for the tomato sauce.

1746
01:56:42,036 --> 01:56:45,247
It was Michael's favorite.
I was making ziti with meat gravy...

1747
01:56:45,415 --> 01:56:47,916
and I'm planning to roast some peppers
over the flames...

1748
01:56:48,084 --> 01:56:52,045
put on some string beans with olive oil.
I had some beautiful cutlets...

1749
01:56:52,213 --> 01:56:53,255
that were cut just right...

1750
01:56:53,423 --> 01:56:56,341
that I was going to fry up as an appetizer.

1751
01:56:56,509 --> 01:56:58,593
So I was home for about an hour.

1752
01:56:58,803 --> 01:57:00,762
My plan was to start the dinner early...

1753
01:57:00,930 --> 01:57:03,473
so Karen and I could unload the guns
Jimmy didn't want...

1754
01:57:03,641 --> 01:57:05,058
then get the package for Lois...

1755
01:57:05,226 --> 01:57:07,769
to take to Atlanta for her trip
later that night.

1756
01:57:08,646 --> 01:57:12,441
I kept looking out the window,
and I saw that the helicopter was gone.

1757
01:57:13,067 --> 01:57:16,570
Michael, keep an eye on the sauce.
Stay here with your Uncle Michael.

1758
01:57:17,697 --> 01:57:21,450
So I asked my brother to watch the sauce,
and Karen and I started out.

1759
01:57:24,370 --> 01:57:26,455
Oh, God. I see it.

1760
01:57:26,706 --> 01:57:29,207
-I see it. Look, it's right there.
-Damn!

1761
01:57:30,418 --> 01:57:31,835
- That's it.
- There it is.

1762
01:57:32,003 --> 01:57:33,628
We got to get to your mother's.

1763
01:57:34,255 --> 01:57:35,505
See, I told you.

1764
01:57:35,715 --> 01:57:37,090
It's funny.

1765
01:57:37,467 --> 01:57:40,469
-It's not the end of the world.
-We're going to your mother's.

1766
01:58:09,040 --> 01:58:12,709
Go inside, tell your mother not to touch
anything outside the house. Nothing.

1767
01:58:12,877 --> 01:58:15,629
We couldn't go to your mother's house?
You had to come here.

1768
01:58:21,177 --> 01:58:22,844
Let's go shopping.

1769
01:58:25,098 --> 01:58:27,224
I'm not nuts,
it's been following me all morning.

1770
01:58:28,392 --> 01:58:29,518
I'm telling you.

1771
01:58:30,520 --> 01:58:33,772
Fine. Fine. He thinks I'm paranoid!

1772
01:58:34,857 --> 01:58:38,235
I should bring him the helicopter,
then we'll see how paranoid I am.

1773
01:58:40,238 --> 01:58:41,863
Come on, let's go inside.

1774
01:58:46,244 --> 01:58:48,161
-Yeah, it's gone.
-I don't hear anything.

1775
01:58:48,329 --> 01:58:49,538
Let's go back to your mother's.

1776
01:59:03,511 --> 01:59:06,054
- They all right?
- Beautiful. They're great.

1777
01:59:06,889 --> 01:59:09,558
Didn't I tell you, you were paranoid?
Didn't I tell him?

1778
01:59:09,725 --> 01:59:11,226
Yeah. I need a hit.

1779
01:59:11,811 --> 01:59:14,813
Want to see helicopters?
Come on, I'll show you helicopters.

1780
01:59:14,981 --> 01:59:17,899
I've seen enough helicopters for one day,
thank you.

1781
01:59:18,901 --> 01:59:23,280
I had to get home and get the
package ready for Lois to take on her trip.

1782
01:59:23,447 --> 01:59:26,241
Also, I had to get to Sandy's to give
the package a whack with quinine.

1783
01:59:27,660 --> 01:59:29,911
Plus, I knew Sandy would get on my ass.

1784
01:59:30,079 --> 01:59:33,790
I had the cooking to finish,
and I had to get Lois ready for her trip.

1785
01:59:33,958 --> 01:59:36,501
-It's Sandy. What is this?
-She's a pain in the ass.

1786
01:59:37,211 --> 01:59:38,879
When are you coming over?

1787
01:59:39,046 --> 01:59:40,922
-In an hour.
-You staying tonight, right?

1788
01:59:41,090 --> 01:59:43,091
I can't. I got my brother tonight.

1789
01:59:43,426 --> 01:59:47,512
Come on, stop.
We'll talk about it later, okay? Goodbye.

1790
01:59:55,146 --> 01:59:57,147
- Hello?
- It's me. You ready?

1791
01:59:58,316 --> 02:00:00,984
Tell Michael not to let the sauce stick.
Keep stirring it.

1792
02:00:01,569 --> 02:00:05,405
-Henry says don't let the sauce stick.
-I'm stirring it.

1793
02:00:05,573 --> 02:00:07,449
-Listen, you know what to do?
-Yeah, yeah.

1794
02:00:07,617 --> 02:00:09,784
Don't "yeah, yeah" me, Lois.
This is important.

1795
02:00:09,952 --> 02:00:12,412
Make sure you leave the house
when you make the call.

1796
02:00:12,580 --> 02:00:15,790
Understand me?
Call from an outside line. I mean it.

1797
02:00:15,958 --> 02:00:19,794
Jesus, you must think I'm dumb. Why
are you bugging me? I know what to do.

1798
02:00:19,962 --> 02:00:22,255
You little hick, just make sure you do it.

1799
02:00:22,423 --> 02:00:23,465
You can be such a pain.

1800
02:00:23,633 --> 02:00:27,594
-Hey! Just do it!
-Okay.

1801
02:00:28,387 --> 02:00:32,891
Un-fucking-believable. All of them.
Every fucking girl in my life.

1802
02:00:34,268 --> 02:00:36,394
-What did he say?
-Nothing.

1803
02:00:36,562 --> 02:00:38,855
What does she do
after she hangs up with me?

1804
02:00:39,023 --> 02:00:42,525
After everything I told her?
After all her "yeah, yeah" bullshit?

1805
02:00:42,693 --> 02:00:45,320
She picks up the phone
and calls from the house.

1806
02:00:45,488 --> 02:00:47,822
If anybody was listening,
they'd know everything.

1807
02:00:47,990 --> 02:00:49,908
They'd know a package
was leaving my house...

1808
02:00:50,076 --> 02:00:53,328
and they'd even have the time and
flight number, thanks to her.

1809
02:00:54,497 --> 02:00:57,165
As soon as I got home, I started cooking.

1810
02:00:57,333 --> 02:00:59,417
I had a few hours until Lois' flight.

1811
02:00:59,585 --> 02:01:01,670
I told my brother to watch the stove.

1812
02:01:01,837 --> 02:01:04,965
All day long the guy's been watching
helicopters and tomato sauce.

1813
02:01:06,425 --> 02:01:11,054
I had to drive over to Sandy's,
mix the stuff, then get back to the gravy.

1814
02:01:22,233 --> 02:01:25,068
Do you think you can come over here,
fuck me, and leave?

1815
02:01:25,444 --> 02:01:27,529
-Come on.
-You got someplace better to go?

1816
02:01:27,697 --> 02:01:30,198
Don't talk like that. Come on.

1817
02:01:30,533 --> 02:01:32,367
-You all right?
-Yeah, sure.

1818
02:01:32,535 --> 02:01:33,576
You believe me?

1819
02:01:34,954 --> 02:01:36,288
Do you believe me?

1820
02:01:36,664 --> 02:01:37,747
Do you believe me?

1821
02:01:40,084 --> 02:01:41,584
-That the last one?
-Yeah.

1822
02:01:51,429 --> 02:01:53,263
You lying son of a bitch. I hate you!

1823
02:02:00,479 --> 02:02:04,274
Please stop feeding the dog
from the table...

1824
02:02:04,442 --> 02:02:06,735
from the plate on top of it. Stop it.

1825
02:02:06,902 --> 02:02:09,237
-I have to.
-You don't have to.

1826
02:02:14,201 --> 02:02:15,660
I got to go home.

1827
02:02:17,705 --> 02:02:19,622
What do you mean, you got to go home?

1828
02:02:19,790 --> 02:02:21,082
I've been carrying this all day.

1829
02:02:21,250 --> 02:02:23,877
We got to start taping it to your leg.
We got to go soon.

1830
02:02:24,045 --> 02:02:25,962
I got to go home and get my hat.

1831
02:02:26,881 --> 02:02:29,090
Forget your fucking hat.
Are you kidding me?

1832
02:02:29,675 --> 02:02:32,427
So I need a trip to Rockaway
because you want your hat?

1833
02:02:32,595 --> 02:02:36,473
I need it, I got to have it.
It's my lucky hat. I never fly without it.

1834
02:02:36,849 --> 02:02:40,769
Lois, do you understand
what we are involved in here?

1835
02:02:41,228 --> 02:02:44,272
I don't care. I need my hat.
I won't fly without it.

1836
02:02:49,403 --> 02:02:52,989
What could I do if she insisted
I drive her home for her goddamn hat?

1837
02:02:53,157 --> 02:02:55,658
I hid the package in the kitchen
and went to take her home.

1838
02:02:55,826 --> 02:02:56,868
A hat?

1839
02:03:06,253 --> 02:03:07,420
What the fuck is this?

1840
02:03:07,838 --> 02:03:10,423
Police! Freeze! Don't you move,
you motherfucker...

1841
02:03:10,591 --> 02:03:13,593
or I'll blow your brains out.
Shut the car off slowly.

1842
02:03:17,598 --> 02:03:19,766
For a second, I thought I was dead.

1843
02:03:19,934 --> 02:03:22,268
But when I heard all the noise,
I knew they were cops.

1844
02:03:22,436 --> 02:03:23,978
Only cops talk that way.

1845
02:03:24,313 --> 02:03:25,480
Don't fucking move.

1846
02:03:25,648 --> 02:03:29,150
If they had been wiseguys,
I wouldn't have heard a thing.

1847
02:03:30,027 --> 02:03:31,653
I would have been dead.

1848
02:03:32,655 --> 02:03:34,114
Michael, lock the door!

1849
02:03:58,639 --> 02:04:01,307
Talk to me. When was the last time
you took a collar?

1850
02:04:01,725 --> 02:04:03,351
Fuckhead, I'm talking to you.

1851
02:04:03,519 --> 02:04:07,188
You don't want to say a fucking word,
don't. I don't really give a fuck.

1852
02:04:07,356 --> 02:04:11,401
You'll do 25 years. See how much
of a good guy you'll be then.

1853
02:04:11,569 --> 02:04:13,695
All day I thought the guys
in the helicopter...

1854
